== Chive Mashed Potatoes ==

Adjust rack to middle position and preheat oven to 425 degrees. Wash and dry produce.

Dice @potatoes{12%ounce} into ½-inch pieces; place in a medium #pot{} with enough salted water to cover by 2 inches. (TIP: For a smoother texture, peel potatoes first.) Bring to a boil and cook until tender, ~{15-20%minutes}. Drain and return potatoes to pot; cover to keep warm.

Quarter @lemon{1}. Thinly slice @chives{¼%ounce}.

== Prosciutto-Wrapped Chicken ==

Pat @chicken cutlets{10%ounce} dry with #paper towels{} and season all over with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Lay two slices of @prosciutto{2%ounce} beside each other on a flat surface. Place a chicken cutlet along bottom of slices; tightly roll up prosciutto around chicken. Repeat with remaining prosciutto and chicken.

Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{1%teaspoon} in a medium pan over medium-high heat. Add wrapped chicken and cook until browned, ~{2-3%minutes} per side. Turn off heat; transfer chicken to a #baking sheet{}. Wipe out pan.

Roast on middle rack until chicken is cooked through, about ~{15%minutes}.

Transfer to a #cutting board{}.

== Chive Mashed Potatoes ==

Mash potatoes with a #potato masher{} or #fork{} until smooth. (TIP: If potatoes have cooled, mash over medium-low heat.)

Stir in chives, half the @cream sauce base{4%ounce}, and 1 tbsp @butter{2%tablespoon}. Season generously with salt and pepper. Keep covered off heat until ready to serve.

== Apricot Glaze & Salad ==

Melt 1 tbsp butter in pan used for chicken over low heat. Whisk in @chicken stock concentrate{1}, @apricot jam{1}, and half the @honey{2%teaspoon}.

When chicken is done, return to pan with any drippings and turn to coat in sauce.

In a #large bowl{}, whisk together half the @Dijon mustard{2%teaspoon}, remaining honey, @olive oil{2%tablespoon}, juice from one lemon wedge, salt, and pepper.

Add @mixed greens{2%ounce} to bowl and toss to coat.

== To Serve ==

Slice chicken crosswise.

Divide chicken, mashed potatoes, and salad between plates. Drizzle any remaining pan sauce over chicken, top salad with @sliced almonds{½%ounce}, and serve.

> Chicken is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 165°.